-- Neovim Configuration Preset
-- Copy this file to preset.lua and customize for your machine
--
-- To use:
--   cp preset.lua.example preset.lua
--   # Edit preset.lua to return your desired preset
--
-- Available presets:
--
--   "full" (default)
--     - All plugins enabled
--     - Best for local editing with good performance
--     - Includes: snacks.nvim picker, nvim-tree, img-clip, project management, sticky-notes
--     - Visual effects: cinnamon scrolling, render-markdown, incline floating names
--
--   "ssh"
--     - Optimized for remote editing over SSH
--     - Excludes plugins that don't work well with latency:
--       * snacks.nvim picker (heavy file scanning)
--       * img-clip (clipboard/GUI-dependent)
--       * project.nvim (heavy directory scanning)
--       * nvim-tree (large directory browsing)
--       * sticky-notes (local file writes)
--     - Still includes: LSP, git, treesitter, completion, navigation
--     - Faster startup, lower bandwidth usage
--
-- Examples:
--   return "full"  -- Use all features (default)
--   return "ssh"   -- Minimal for SSH connections
--
-- You can also use environment variable:
--   NVIM_PRESET=ssh nvim

return "full"
